subject: Tennis
lead_paragraph: James Blake looked rusty before rallying to beat the unheralded Dudi Sela, 7-6 (2), 6-2, in a first-round match at the Indianapolis Tennis Championships. The top-seeded Blake had not played since losing to Rainer Schüttler in the second round at Wimbledon last month.
